## 5. Code Patterns & Anti-Patterns

### ✅ DO

- Use Flask's global `JOBS` dict with thread-safe locks
- Poll `/api/jobs/<job_id>` every 1-2 sec from React
- Check path traversal on all file downloads
- Use AudioWorker persistent GPU engine (never re-load model)
- Write Playwright tests BEFORE implementing features (TDD)
- Update `progress.md` after every task completion

### ❌ DON'T

- Load TTS model per-request (use persistent AudioWorker)
- Trust Content-Disposition header (extract from multipart boundary)
- Return inconsistent API formats
- Use regex for character detection (BookNLP is installed)
- Skip Playwright tests before claiming work is done
- Merge unrelated cleanups into feature work

